Spending Account (FSA)?**  \nA FSA (Flexible Spending Account) allows use of the funds an individual has designated to be set aside pre-tax for medical expenses, typically with their employer, when selecting healthcare programs during the previous year.\n\n### ** What types of purchases are FSA eligible?** \nOver-the-counter medical supplies and equipment are considered reimbursable by an FSA account in 2011 and include the following categories: \n - Contact lens solution\n - Prescription contact lenses with correction only\n - Diagnostic devices (i.e. blood pressure and blood glucose   self.__next_f.push([1,"50f:T421,### **Why is this item marked as FSA Eligible?** \nThis item is marked with the following icon as FSA eligible to identify that it MAY be purchased using a Flexible Spending Account (FSA).\n\n###  ** What is a Flexible Spending Account (FSA)?**  \nA FSA (Flexible Spending Account) allows use of the funds an individual has designated to be set aside pre-tax for medical expenses, typically with their employer, when selecting healthcare programs during the previous year.\n\n### ** What types of purchases are FSA eligible?** \nOver-the-counter medical supplies and equipment are considered reimbursable by an FSA account in 2011 and include the following categories: \n - Contact lens solution\n - Prescription contact lenses with correction only\n - Diagnostic devices (i.e. blood pressure and blood glucose monitors)\n - Durable medical equipment and goods\n - Insulin\n - Prescription medications\n\n***Note:*** *Although the IRS sets guidelines for FSA programs, individual employers have the final determination of which expenses are covered by their FSA programs.*"])
 </script>

 <script>
  self.__next_f.push([1,"510:T421,### **Why is this item marked as FSA Eligible?** \nThis item is marked with the following icon as FSA eligible to identify that it MAY be purchased using a Flexible Spending Account (FSA).\n\n###  ** What is a Flexible Spending Account (FSA)?**  \nA FSA (Flexible Spending Account) allows use of the funds an individual has designated to be set aside pre-tax for medical expenses, typically with their employer, when selecting healthcare programs during the previous year.\n\n### ** What types of purchases are FSA eligible?** \nOver-the-counter medical supplies and equipment are considered reimbursable by an FSA account in 2011 and include the following categories: \n - Contact lens solution\n - Prescription contact lenses with correction only\n - Diagnostic devices (i.e. blood pressure and blood glucose monitors)\n - Durable medical equipment and goods\n - Insulin\n - Prescription medications\n\n***Note:*** *Although the IRS sets guidelines for FSA programs, individual employers have the final determination of which expenses are covered by their FSA programs.*"])
 </script>

  self.__next_f.push([1,"511:T421,### **Why is this item marked as FSA Eligible?** \nThis item is marked with the following icon as FSA eligible to identify that it MAY be purchased using a Flexible Spending Account (FSA).\n\n###  ** What is a Flexible Spending Account (FSA)?**  \nA FSA (Flexible Spending Account) allows use of the funds an individual has designated to be set aside pre-tax for medical expenses, typically with their employer, when selecting healthcare programs during the previous year.\n\n### ** What types of purchases are FSA eligible?** \nOver-the-counter medical supplies and equipment are considered reimbursable by an FSA account in 2011 and include the following categories: \n - Contact lens solution\n - Prescription contact lenses with correction only\n - Diagnostic devices (i.e. blood pressure and blood glucose monitors)\n - Durable medical equipment and goods\n - Insulin\n - Prescription medications\n\n***Note:*** *Although the IRS sets guidelines for FSA programs, individual employers have the final determination of which expenses are covered by their FSA programs.*"])

 <script data-nscript="afterInteractive" id="kmsi">
  const WCS_TIMEOUT = 60 * 60 * 1000; // 60 minutes
        
        const wcsUtils = {
            getCookie: function getCookie(name) {
                var _a;
                const value = '; ' + document.cookie;
                const parts = value.split('; ' + name+'=');
                if (parts.length === 2)
                    return (_a = parts.pop()) === null || _a === void 0 ? void 0 : _a.split(";").shift();
            },
            isWcsSessionExpired: function isWcsSessionExpired() {
                try {
                    const kmsi = wcsUtils.getCookie("kmsi");
                    if (typeof kmsi != "undefined" && kmsi != null && kmsi.indexOf("true") >= 0) {
                        const hashedUserId = wcsUtils.getCookie("hashedUserId");
                        if (!hashedUserId) {
                            return true;
                        }
                        
                        const [ksmiBoolean, ksmiTimestamp] = kmsi.split("_");
                        if (ksmiBoolean && ksmiTimestamp) {
                            const timestamp = parseInt(ksmiTimestamp);
                            return Date.now() - timestamp > WCS_TIMEOUT;
                        }
                    }
                    return false;
                }
                catch (e) {
                    return false;
                }
            },
            isKmsiSession: function isKmsiSession() {
                try {
                    const kmsi = wcsUtils.getCookie("kmsi");
                    if (typeof kmsi === "undefined" || kmsi === null || kmsi === "false") {
                        return false;
                    }
                }
                catch (e) {
                    console.log(e);
                }
                return true;
            },

            kmsi: function kmsi() {
                let ksmiApiCallCount = 0;
                try {
                    if (wcsUtils.isKmsiSession() && wcsUtils.isWcsSessionExpired()) {
                        const xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
                        xhr.open("GET", "/kmsi", false);
                        xhr.onreadystatechange = function () {
                            if (xhr.readyState === 4) {
                                if (xhr.status === 200) {
                                    try {
                                        const t = JSON.parse(xhr.responseText);
                                        if ("true" === t.kmsi) {
                                            ksmiApiCallCount = 0;
                                        }
                                        else if (ksmiApiCallCount < 3) {
                                            ksmiApiCallCount++;
                                            wcsUtils.kmsi();
                                        }
                                    }
                                    catch (e) {
                                        console.error(e);
                                    }
                                }
                                else {
                                    console.error("Request failed with status: /kmsi ", xhr.status);
                                    if (wcsUtils.isWcsSessionExpired()) {
                                        window.location.href = "/LogonForm?prompt=false&fromPage=/"; // Redirect if conditions are met
                                    }
                                }
                            }
                        };
                        xhr.send();
                    }
                }
                catch (error) {
                    console.log(error);
                }
            },
            isWcsSessionEstablished: function isWcsSessionEstablished() {
                try {
                    const wcsSession = wcsUtils.getCookie("hashedUserId");
                    return !!wcsSession;
                }
                catch (e) {
                    console.log(e);
                }
                return false;
            },
        };
        wcsUtils.kmsi();
 </script>

 <script data-airgap-id="6" data-nscript="afterInteractive" id="AdobeScript" src="https://assets.adobedtm.com/db2abc551d12/237ca126a76b/launch-01eecb8ff534.min.js">
 </script>
 <script>
  _satellite["_runScript1"](function(event, target, Promise) {
window.adobeopt = window.adobeopt || {};
window.digitalDataEvents = window.digitalDataEvents || [];

adobeopt.extend = function (destObj /*, ...arg1, arg2 */) {
  for (let i = 1; i < arguments.length; i++) {
    if ( typeof arguments[i] == "object" ) {
      for (let key in arguments[i]) {
        destObj[key] = arguments[i][key];
      }
    }
  }
  return destObj;
};
function AoptModule(modname, props) {
  this.modname = modname;
  if (props !== undefined) {
    adobeopt.addProps(props);
  }
}
adobeopt.extend( AoptModule.prototype, {
  addProps: function (props) {
    adobeopt.extend(this, props);
  },
  ifdiag: function () { },
  diag: function () { },
  log: function () { },
  inspect: function () { },
  resolve: function () { },
  warn: function () { },
  error: function (type, details) {
    console.error("~ aopt CAUGHT exception", type, details);
  },
  exception: function (mod, ex) {
    this.error.apply(this, arguments);
  },
  trySafe: function (fncname, fnc) {
    let aoptmod = this;
    try {
      return fnc();
    } catch (ex) {
      aoptmod.error(fncname, ex);
    }
  },
  tryWrap: function (fncname, fnc) {
    let aoptmod = this;
    return function () {
      try {
        return fnc.apply(this, arguments);
      } catch (ex) {
        aoptmod.error(fncname, ex);
      }
    }
  }
} );
adobeopt.extend( adobeopt, {
  AoptModule: AoptModule,
  modules: {},
  modulesByDesc: {},
  fncNil: function () { },
  fncTrue: function () { return true },
  fncFalse: function () { return false },
  configs: {},
  isEmpty: function (val) {
    return (val === undefined || val == null || val.length <= 0) ? true : false;
  },
  reFilterStr: function (f, defVal) {
    if (typeof f == "string" && f.length > 0) {
      try {
        f = "(" + f.split("*").join(".*").split("+").join(".+") + ")";
        return RegExp(f);
      } catch (e) { }
    }
    return { test: defVal ? adobeopt.fncTrue : adobeopt.fncFalse };
  },
  config: function (n, def) {
    if (!adobeopt.configs.hasOwnProperty(n)) {
      adobeopt.configs[n] = sessionStorage.getItem("aopt_" + n) || localStorage.getItem("aopt_" + n);
    }
    return adobeopt.configs[n];
  },
  setConfig: function (n, v, useSessionStorage) {
    (useSessionStorage === true ? sessionStorage : localStorage).setItem("aopt_" + n, v);
  },
  hasConfig: function (n) {
    return adobeopt.config(n) !== null;
  },
  ifConfig: function (n, fnc) {
    return adobeopt.hasConfig(n) ? fnc(adobeopt.config(n)) : null;
  },
  newdiag: function () { return adobeopt.fncNil },
  module: function (modname, modprops) {
    let mod = adobeopt.modules[modname];
    if (mod === undefined) {
      mod = new AoptModule(modname);
      adobeopt.modules[modname] = mod;
    }
    if (typeof modprops == "object") {
      adobeopt.extend(mod, modprops);
      if (mod.desc && !adobeopt.modulesByDesc.hasOwnProperty(mod.desc)) {
        adobeopt.modulesByDesc[mod.desc] = mod;
      }
    }
    return mod;
  },
  deepRef: function (obj, ref, def) {
    return ref.split(".").reduce((obj, level) => obj && obj[level], obj) || def;
  },
  deepRefMake: function (obj, ref) {
    return ref.split(".").reduce( (obj, level) => {
      if ( typeof obj[level] !== "object" ) {
        obj[level] = {};
      }
      return obj[level];
    }, obj);
  },
  fillin: function (destObj /*, ...arg1, arg2 */) {
    for (let i = 1; i < arguments.length; i++) {
      for (let key in arguments[i]) {
        let v = destObj[key];
        if (v) {
          destObj[key] = arguments[i][key];
        }
      }
    }
    return destObj;
  },
  propGetOrSetDefault: function (obj, propname, def) {
    if (!obj.hasOwnProperty(propname)) {
      return (obj[propname] = def);
    }
    return obj[propname];
  },
  json: function (jsonStr, def) { // error catching json
    if (typeof jsonStr === "string" && jsonStr !== "") {
      try {
        return JSON.parse(jsonStr);
      } catch (ex) { }
    }
    return def || {};
  },
  jsonCookie: function (cookieName, def) {
    return adobeopt.json(_satellite.cookie.get(cookieName), def);
  },
  jsonCookieRef: function (cookieName, ref, def) {
    return adobeopt.deepRef(adobeopt.json(_satellite.cookie.get(cookieName)), ref, def);
  },
  reExtract(re, str, def) {
    let match = str.match(re);
    return match && match.length == 2 ? match[1] : def;
  },
  dictFromCssStr: function (str, destDict) {
    destDict = destDict || {};
    try {
      if (typeof str === "string") {
        str.split(";").forEach(function (prop) {
          var nvp = prop.split(":", 2);
          if (nvp.length == 2 && nvp[0].length > 0 ) {
            destDict[nvp[0]] = nvp[1];
          } else {
            // report error
          }
        });
      }
    } catch (e) { 
      // report error
    }
    return destDict;
  },
  sessionIncCounter: function (name) {
    try {
      let ct = parseInt(sessionStorage.getItem(name)) || 0;
      sessionStorage.setItem(name, ++ct);
      return ct;
    } catch (e) {
      // fall through
    }
    return 0;
  },
  linkTag: function (l) {
    l = l.toLowerCase().replace("https://", "").replace("http://", "");
    var ich = l.indexOf("/");
    if (ich === -1) {
      return "";
    }
    return l.slice(ich + 1).replace(".html", "").replace(/[^a-z]+/g, "");
  },
  queryParam: function (paramName, def) {
    const p = adobeopt.queryParamValues[ paramName.toLowerCase() ];
    return typeof p == "string" && p !== '' ? p : def;
  },
  debounce: function (func, wait, immediate) {
    var timeout;
    return function () {
      var context = this, args = arguments;
      var later = function () {
        timeout = null;
        if (!immediate) func.apply(context, args);
      };
      var callNow = immediate && !timeout;
      clearTimeout(timeout);
      timeout = setTimeout(later, wait);
      if (callNow) func.apply(context, args);
    };
  },
  cleanUrl: function( fromUrl ) {
    try {
      const url = new URL( fromUrl, window.location.origin );
      // remove encryted user context info, not useful
      url.searchParams.delete("krypto");
      // remove canonical info from path
      if ( url.pathname.indexOf(".product.") > -1 ) {
          // strip canonical portion of path to keep v74 uniform
          var myRegexp = /(\.product\..*\.html)/g;
          var match = myRegexp.exec( url.pathname );
          if ( match ) {
            url.pathname = "/" + match[1];
          }
      }
      return url.toString();
    } catch ( ex ) {
      console.log(ex);
      return fromUrl;
    }
  },
  logBeacon: function(){}
});

adobeopt.queryParamValues = {};
try {
    const params = new URLSearchParams(window.location.search);
    for(var value of params.keys()) {
        adobeopt.queryParamValues[ value.toLowerCase() ] = params.get(value);
    }
} catch ( ex ) { console.error( ex ) }
try {
    let deferredQsParams = adobeopt.json( localStorage.getItem( "aopt-deferred-attribution" ) );
    if ( Object.keys(deferredQsParams).length > 0 ) {
       localStorage.removeItem("aopt-deferred-attribution");
        for ( let paramName in deferredQsParams ) {
            adobeopt.queryParamValues[ paramName.toLowerCase() ] = deferredQsParams[paramName];
        }
    }
} catch ( ex ) { console.error( ex ) }

if ( typeof adobeopt.diagInit == "function" ) {
  adobeopt.diagInit( AoptModule );
}

let modTarget = adobeopt.module("target");
let modLaunch = adobeopt.module("launch");

adobeopt.diagAopt = adobeopt.fncNil; // REVIEW, remove references
adobeopt.diagTarget = adobeopt.fncNil;
adobeopt.diagLaunch = adobeopt.fncNil;

let when = adobeopt.when = adobeopt.module("adobeopt.when");
let tag = adobeopt.tag = adobeopt.module("adobeopt.tag");
let dom = adobeopt.dom = adobeopt.module("adobeopt.dom");
let reco = adobeopt.reco = adobeopt.module("adobeopt.reco");

if (adobeopt.isDiag) {

  adobeopt.ifConfig("launchevents", function () {
    window._satellite._monitors = window._satellite._monitors || [];
    window._satellite._monitors.push({
      ruleTriggered: function (event) {
        modLaunch.log(["rule", event.rule.name, "fired"].join(":"), event.rule);
      },
      ruleCompleted: function (event) {
        modLaunch.log(["rule", event.rule.name, "completed"].join(":"), event.rule);
      },
      ruleConditionFailed: function (event) {
        modLaunch.log(["rule", event.rule.name, "notmet"].join(":"), event.rule, event.condition);
      }
    });
  });

}

if ( _satellite.getVar("useAlloyTarget") == false ) {

  modTarget.trySafe("initMeta", function () {

    window.ttMETA = window.ttMETA || [];

    document.addEventListener("at-request-succeeded", function (e) {
      var tokens = e.detail.responseTokens;
      if (!adobeopt.isEmpty(tokens)) {
        tokens.forEach(function (token) {
          var props = {
            'CampaignName': token["activity.name"],
            'CampaignId': token["activity.id"],
            'RecipeName': token["experience.name"],
            'RecipeId': token["experience.id"],
            'OfferId': token["option.id"],
            'OfferName': token["option.name"],
            'LatestEMID': token["profile.LatestEMID"],
            'MboxName': e.detail.mbox
          };
          window.ttMETA.push(props);
          modTarget.diag("at-request-succeeded", props);
        });
      }
    });

    if (adobeopt.isDiag) {
      modTarget.events = ["at-library-loaded", "at-request-start", "at-request-succeeded", "at-request-failed", "at-content-rendering-start", "at-content-rendering-succeeded", "at-content-rendering-failed", "at-content-rendering-no-offers", "at-content-rendering-redirect"];
      modTarget.diag("diag:is adobe inited", window.adobe !== undefined, adobeopt.deepRef(window, "adobe.target.events") !== undefined);

      let ttMetaEvent = function (e) { modTarget.diag("event", e) };
      for (var adobe_msg in modTarget.events) {
        document.addEventListener(adobe_msg, ttMetaEvent);
      }
    }

    return "complete";

  });
}

adobeopt.alloy = function( event, data ) {
  return alloy(event, data)
  .then(response => {
    adobeopt.logTargetActivity(response);
    return response;
  })
}

adobeopt.when.poll = function (pollSettings /* optional */, func) {
  if (arguments.length == 1 && typeof arguments[0] === "function") {
    pollSettings = { func: arguments[0] };
  }
  let initSettings = adobeopt.extend({
    func: func,
    pollms: 250,
    pollmax: 20,
    intervalId: 0,
    mod: adobeopt.when,
    rejectOnTimeout: false
  }, pollSettings);
  pollSettings.name = pollSettings?.name || pollSettings?.mod?.name || "adobeopt.when.poll";
  function poll() {
    let settings = this.settings;
    let trace = [settings.pollmax];
    settings.val = settings.func(settings);
    if (settings.val !== undefined && settings.val !== null && settings.val !== false) {
      trace.push("resolved");
      settings.resolve(settings.val);
    } else if (--settings.pollmax < 1) {
      trace.push("rejected:timeout");
      if ( settings.rejectOnTimeout ) {
        settings.reject(new Error("timeout"));
      }
    } else {
      if (settings.intervalId === 0) {
        trace.push("setInterval");
        settings.intervalId = setInterval(settings.nextPoll, settings.pollms);
      } else {
        trace.push("wait next interval");
      }
      settings.mod.diag( settings.name, trace);
      return;
    }
    if (settings.intervalId) {
      clearInterval(settings.intervalId);
    }
    settings.mod.diag( settings.name, trace);
  }
  function pollPromise(resolve, reject) {
    initSettings.resolve = resolve;
    initSettings.reject = reject;
    initSettings.nextPoll = poll.bind({ settings: initSettings });
    initSettings.nextPoll();
  }
  return new Promise(pollPromise);
}

adobeopt.when.elementExistsPoll = function (selector, settings) {
  return adobeopt.when.poll(adobeopt.extend(settings || {}, { name: "adobeopt.when.elementReadyPoll", selector: selector }), function (settings) {
    return document.querySelector(selector);
  });
};

adobeopt.when.elementExistsObserver = function (selector, settings) {
  settings = settings || {};
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    let el = document.querySelector(selector);
    if (el) {
      resolve(el);
      return;
    }
    new MutationObserver((mutationRecords, observer) => {
      // Query for elements matching the specified selector
      Array.from(document.querySelectorAll(selector)).forEach((element) => {
        resolve(element);
        //Once we have resolved we don't need the observer anymore.
        observer.disconnect();
      });
    }).observe(document.documentElement, {
      childList: true,
      subtree: true
    });
  });
};

adobeopt.when.elementExists = adobeopt.when.elementExistsPoll;

adobeopt.when.refDefined = function (ref, pollsettings) {
  return adobeopt.when.poll(adobeopt.extend(pollsettings || {}, { name: "adobeopt.when.refDefined", ref: ref }), function (settings) {
    return adobeopt.deepRef(window, ref);
  });
};

adobeopt.isJqueryLoaded = function() {
  if ( _satellite.getVar("isPageModernized?") ) {
    return false;
  }
  return (typeof window.jQuery !== "function" || window.$.slick === undefined);
}

if ( _satellite.getVar("isPageModernized?") ) {
  adobeopt.when.jQueryReadyPromise = new Promise(()=>{});
} else {
  adobeopt.when.jQueryReadyPromise = adobeopt.when.poll({ name: "adobeopt.when.jQueryReady" }, function (settings) {
    if (typeof window.$ !== "function" || window.$.slick === undefined) {
      return null;
    }
    return window.$;
  });
}

adobeopt.when.jQueryReady = function (fnc) {
  return fnc ? adobeopt.when.jQueryReadyPromise.then(fnc) : adobeopt.when.jQueryReadyPromise;
}

adobeopt.when.domReadyPromise = new Promise(resolve => {
  if (document.readyState === "loading") {
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', resolve)
  } else {
    resolve();
  }
});

adobeopt.when.domReady = function (fnc) {
  return fnc ? adobeopt.when.domReadyPromise.then(fnc) : adobeopt.when.domReadyPromise;
}

adobeopt.when.pageLoadedPromise = new Promise(resolve => {
  if (document.readyState === "complete") {
    window.addEventListener("load", resolve);
  } else {
    resolve();
  }
});

adobeopt.when.pageLoaded = function (fnc) {
  return fnc ? adobeopt.when.pageLoadedPromise.then(fnc) : adobeopt.when.pageLoadedPromise;
};

adobeopt.when.targetReadyPromise = new Promise(resolve => {
  if (adobeopt.deepRef(window, "adobe.target")) {
    resolve();
  } else {
    document.addEventListener("at-library-loaded", function () {
      resolve();
    });
  }
});

adobeopt.when.targetReady = function (fnc) {
  return fnc ? adobeopt.when.targetReadyPromise.then(fnc) : adobeopt.when.targetReadyPromise;
}

dom.eventHandlers = { /* click: { delegates:[] } */ }; // click, submit, etc

function objPropDef(obj, name, def) {
  if (obj.hasOwnProperty(name)) {
    return obj[name];
  }
  return (obj[name] = (typeof def == "function" ? def() : def));
}

// add a listener
dom.on = adobeopt.listen = function (props) {
  // props.event: "click/submit/etc"
  // props.sel: "css selector"
  // props.selTarget: "css selector - delegate"
  // props.selContainer: "css for control area"
  // props.fire: properties to fire to analytics
  // props.handler: handler to call

  if ( ! adobeopt.isJqueryLoaded() ) {
    return;
  }

  const eventHandler = objPropDef(dom.eventHandlers, props.eventName, {});
  let elementHandler = objPropDef(eventHandler, props.sel, function () {
    let elements = $(props.sel);
    if (elements.length == 0) {
      // diag("warning: no elements found", props);
    }
    let handler = {
      eventName: props.eventName,
      delegates: []
    }
    handler.listener = function (event) { dom.dispatchEvent(handler, this, event) } // closure for handler (review: bind?)
    $(elements).each((i, element) => {
      element.addEventListener(props.eventName, handler.listener, { collect: true }); // passive:true, collect phase, we're not UI, just analytics
    });
    return handler;
  });
  elementHandler.delegates.push(props); // props can be dehydrated, we don't even look until something happens in this area
  return elementHandler;
};

dom.elementContext = function (element, event) {
  return {
    event: event, // for template references
    target: event.target || element, // for template references
    element: element,
    rootElement: element,
    _cancelBeacon: false,
    window: window
  };
};

dom.dispatchEvent = function (handler, element, event) {
  dom.diag("root delegate hit", handler);
  dom.dispatchEventDelegates(handler, dom.elementContext(element, event));
};

dom.dispatchEventDelegates = function (handler, context) {
  const delegates = handler.delegates;
  for (let i = 0; i < delegates.length; i++) {
    let delegate = delegates[i];
    if (dom.elementMatchesDelegate(context.element, delegate)) {
      let props = adobeopt.extend({ props: delegate }, context);
      diag("dispatchEventDelegates:matched", props);
      try {
        tag.applyObj(props.fire, props, tag.analyticsBeacon);
      } catch (ex) { dom.exception(ex) }
    }
  }
};

dom.elementMatchesDelegate = function (element, delegate) {

  if ( ! adobeopt.isJqueryLoaded() ) {
    return
  }

  // let props = tag.getPropHyd( context, delegates, i ); // allows hydration, otherwise reference directly
  let props = delegate;
  if (props.selTarget && !$(element).is(props.selTarget)) { // !event.target.matches( props._elementSelector ) // use jquery for selector extensiosn like :contains
    // diag( "did not match selTarget", props );
    return false;
  }
  if (props.selExclude && $(element).is(props.selExclude)) { // !event.target.matches( props._elementSelector ) // use jquery for selector extensiosn like :contains
    // diag( "did not match, excluded by selExclude", props );
    return false;
  }
  // diag( "matched", props );
  return true;
}

dom.delegateFullSelector = function (delegate) {
  return delegate.sel + " " + delegate.selTarget;
}

// DOM QUERY

dom.isNodeList = function( elements ) {
  return NodeList.prototype.isPrototypeOf(elements);
}
dom.isNode = function( element ) {
  return Node.prototype.isPrototypeOf(element);
}
function QueryNodeList( nodeList ) {
  this.nodeLists = [];
  this.length = 0;
  if ( nodeList ) {
      this.appendNodeList( nodeList );
  }
}
dom.QueryNodeList = QueryNodeList;
adobeopt.extend( QueryNodeList.prototype, {
  appendNodeList: function( nodeList ) {
      if ( adobeopt.dom.isNodeList(nodeList) && nodeList.length > 0 ) {
          this.nodeLists.push( nodeList );
          this.length = nodeList.length;
      } else if ( adobeopt.dom.isNode( nodeList )) {
          this.nodeLists.push( [nodeList] );
          this.length += 1;
      } else {
          // warning?
      }
      return this;
  },
  forEach: function( fnc ) {
      let index = -1;
      // REVIEW: we do this so that we don't need to keep converting nodeLists to arrays in order
      // to concatenate them. The important thing is that .appendNodeList is used add them
      // and .forEach is always used to enumerate them. With that we can swap out the implementation
      // Array.forEach does not allow exiting early so we enumerate ourselves
      for ( let iNodeList = 0; iNodeList < this.nodeLists.length ; iNodeList++ ) {
          let nodeList = this.nodeLists[iNodeList];
          for ( let iNode = 0; iNode < nodeList.length ; iNode++ ) {
              let node = nodeList[iNode];
              if ( false === fnc( node, index++ ) ) { 
                  return this;
              }
          }
      }
      return this;
  },
  each: function( fnc ) { // compatible with jQuery's .each use of this in fnc call
      return this.forEach( function( node, index ) {
          return fnc.call( node, index, node )
      });
  },
  firstNode: function( fnc ) {
      let firstNode = this.nodeLists?.[0]?.[0];
      if ( fnc && firstNode ) {
          return fnc( firstNode );
      }
      return firstNode;
  },
  first: function() {
      return new QueryNodeList( this.firstNode() );
  },
  find: function( selector ) {
      let result = new QueryNodeList();
      this.forEach( ( node ) => result.appendNodeList( node.querySelectorAll( selector ) ) );
      return result;
  },
  closest: function( selector ) {
      let result = new QueryNodeList();
      this.forEach( ( node ) => result.appendNodeList( node.closest( selector ) ) );
      return result;
  },
  attr: function( attrName, attrValue ) {
      let node = this.firstNode();
      if ( node ) {
          if ( attrValue !== undefined ) {
              node.setAttribute( attrName, attrValue );
              return this;
          } else {
              return node.getAttribute( attrName, attrValue );
          }
      }
      return undefined;
  },
  html: function( htmlValue ) {
      return this.firstNode( (node) => {
          if ( htmlValue !== undefined ) {
              node.innerHTML = htmlValue;
              return this;
          }
          return node.innerHTML;
      });
  },
  outerHtml: function( htmlValue ) {
      return this.firstNode( (node) => {
          if ( htmlValue !== undefined ) {
              node.outerHTML = htmlValue;
              return this;
          }
          return node.outerHTML;
      });
  },
  text: function( textValue ) {
      return this.firstNode( (node) => {
          if ( textValue !== undefined ) {
              node.innerText = textValue;
              return this;
          }
          return node.innerText;
      });
  },    
  closestAttr: function( attrName, def ) {
      let node = this.firstNode();
      if ( node ) {
          let attrNode = node.closest("["+attrName+"]");
          if ( attrNode !== null ) {
              return attrNode.getAttribute(attrName);
          }
      }
      return def;
  },
  css: function( propName, propValue ) {
      return this.forEach( ( node, index ) => { node.style[propName] = propValue } );
  },
  contains: function( text ) { // like jQuery's :contains() selector
      let result = new QueryNodeList();
      this.forEach( ( node ) => {
          if ( RegExp(text).test(node.textContent) ) {
              result.appendNodeList( node )
          }
      } );
      return result;
  },
  on: function( events /* , selector, data, handler */   ) { // like jQuerys .on() without data

      return this;
  }

} );

function createElementStyle( props ) {
  let cssParts = [];
  Object.entries(props).forEach(([cssSelector, cssProps]) => {
    // selector
    if ( cssSelector == "type" ) {
      return;
    }
    let styleParts = [];
    Object.entries(cssProps).forEach(([cssAttrib, cssValue]) => {
      styleParts.push( cssAttrib + ":" + cssValue );
    });
    cssParts.push( cssSelector + " {" + styleParts.join(";") + "}\n" );
  });
  return cssParts.join("\n");
}

function createElement( props, parentElement ) {
  if ( typeof props == "function" ) {
    props = props();
  }
  if ( typeof props == "string" ) {
    props = { type:"text", text:props };
  }
  if ( typeof props !== "object" ) {
    return null;
  }
  if ( Array.isArray( props ) ) {
    props.forEach( (childElement) => {
      createElement( childElement, parentElement );
    });
    return;
  }
  if ( props.omit === true ) { // easy way to omit w/o a function
    return null;
  }
  if ( typeof props.type !== "string" ) {
    return null;
  }
  if ( props.type == "text" ) {
    let textElement = document.createTextNode( props.text );
    if ( parentElement ) {
      parentElement.appendChild( textElement );
    }
    return textElement;
  }
  const element = document.createElement( props.type );
  if ( parentElement ) {
    parentElement.appendChild( element );
  }
  Object.entries(props).forEach(([key, value]) => {
      switch( key ) {
          case "class":
              element.classList.add(value);
              return;
          case "dataset":
              Object.entries(value).forEach(([dataKey, dataValue]) => {
                  element.dataset[dataKey] = dataValue;
              });
              return;
          case "text":
              element.textContent = value;
              return;
          case "events":
              Object.entries(props).forEach(([eventName, eventHandler]) => {
                element.addEventListener( eventName, eventHandler );
              });
              return;
          case "children":
              createElement( value, element );
              return;
          default:
              if ( typeof value == "string" ) {
                element.setAttribute(key, value);
              }
          case "type": // handled above
              return;
      }
  });
  return element;
}
function placeElement( placementProps, elementProps ) {
  let element = createElement( elementProps );
  let existing = document.getElementById( elementProps.id );
  if ( existing ) {
    existing.replaceWith( element );
  } else {
    let placement = document.querySelector( placementProps.selector );
    if ( typeof placement[placementProps.method] == "function" ) {
      // before, after, append, prepend
      placement[placementProps.method]( element );
    }
  }
  return element;
}
dom.createElement = createElement;

dom.query = function ( arg ) {
  if ( typeof arg == "string" ) {
      arg = document.querySelectorAll( arg );
  }
  return new QueryNodeList( arg );
};
dom.queryFirst = function ( arg ) {
  if ( typeof arg == "string" ) {
      arg = document.querySelector( arg );
  }
  return new QueryNodeList( arg );
};

// .on has a syntax easy to translate from jquery
adobeopt.on = function (eventName, sel) { // ... [selTarget], fncHandler, [data] )
  if (typeof sel == "object" || sel == "") {
    sel = "body"; // fully delegated listener
  }
  let props = {
    eventName: eventName,
    sel: sel
  }
  if (arguments.length == 3) {
    props.selTarget = "";
    props.fncLegacyListener = arguments[2];
  } else if (arguments.length == 4) {
    props.selTarget = arguments[2];
    props.fncLegacyListener = arguments[3];
  }
  adobeopt.listen(props);
}

adobeopt.legacyListener = function (context, params) {
  context._fncLegacyListener.call(context.element, context.event);
  // now process beacon
}

// firing triggered values
tag.analyticsBeacon = function (event, props, context) {
  tag.diag("analyticsBeacon", context);
  if (context._cancelBeacon == true) {
    tag.diag("canceling per context._cancelBeacon");
    return;
  }
  context.props = adobeopt.extend({}, props); // make a copy for resolving
  tag.resolveValues(context, context.props);
  digitalDataEvents.push(context.props);
};

// props; tools for collecting props associated with event

tag.getObjRef = function (obj, ref, def) { // deep reference value in object (default:window)
  def = (def == undefined) ? "" : def;
  try {
    for (var p = ref.split("."); p.length && obj != undefined;) {
      obj = obj[p.shift()];
    }
  } catch (e) { return def }
  return obj != undefined ? obj : def;
};
let getObjRef = tag.getObjRef;

tag.applyObj = function (obj, params, defHandler) {
  if (typeof obj == "function") {
    return obj(params);
  }
  return tag.getObjRef(adobeopt, obj._type, defHandler || adobeopt.unknown)(obj, params);
};

tag.renderRef = function (context, ref) {
  try {
    return tag.resolveValue(context, tag.getObjRef(context, ref));
  } catch (ex) { }
  return "";
};
tag.renderTmpl = function (context, template) {
  return template.replace(/\${(.*?)}/g, function (match) {
    return tag.renderRef(context, match.split(/\${|}/).filter(Boolean)[0]);
  });
};

tag.resolveValue = function( context, val ) {
  let itermax = 0;
  try {
      do { 
          switch( typeof val ) {
              case "function":
                  val = val( context );
                  continue;
              case "string":
                  if ( val.indexOf("${") == -1 ) {
                      return val;
                  }
                  val = tag.renderTmpl( context, val );
                  continue;
              case "boolean":
              case "number":
              case "bigint":
                  return obj[propName] = String(val);
              case "undefined":
              case "object":
                  if ( Array.isArray(val) ) {
                      return tag.findValue.apply( context,  )
                  }
                  return "";
          }
      } while ( ++itermax < 10 ); // itermax for circular refs
  } catch ( ex ) {
      tag.log(ex);
  };
  return "";
};
tag.resolveProp = function( context, obj, propName, def ) {
  let val = tag.resolveValue( context, obj[propName] );
  if ( typeof val == "string" ) {
      obj[propName] = val;
  }
  return obj[propName];
};
tag.resolveValues = function (context, obj, destObj) {
  destObj = destObj || obj;
  for (let key in obj) {
    tag.resolveProp(context, obj, key);
  }
};

tag.hasValue = function (v) {
  switch (typeof v) {
    case "string":
      return v.length > 0;
    case "number":
    case "boolean":
    case "bigint":
      return true;
  }
  return false;
};

tag.findValue = function( context ) {
  for ( let iarg = 1 ; iarg < arguments.length ; iarg++ ) {
      let ret = tag.resolveValue( context, arguments[iarg] );
      if ( tag.hasValue(ret) ) {
          return ret;
      }
  }
  return null;
};

tag.findFirstValue = function (context, values) {
  for (let iarg = 0; iarg < values.length; iarg++) {
    let ret = tag.resolveValue(context, values[iarg]);
    if (tag.hasValue(ret)) {
      return ret;
    }
  }
  return null;
};


// dom scrape functions

tag.closestWide = function (element, selector, maxParents) {
  if ( ! adobeopt.isJqueryLoaded() ) {
    return
  }

  let max = maxParents || 7;
  var f;
  try {
    do {
      f = $(element).find(selector).first();
      if (f.length > 0) {
        return f;
      }
      element = element.parentElement;
    } while (--max && element != null && element.nodeName != "BODY");
  } catch (ex) { tag.exception(ex) }
  return $().empty();
};


// diagnostic functions

dom.diagShowDelegates = function (styleAttribs) {
  if ( ! adobeopt.isJqueryLoaded() ) {
    return
  }

  styleAttribs = styleAttribs || '::before { content:" "; position:absolute; width: 40px; height: 20px; background-color:orange; opacity:0.5 }';
  styleAttribs = "{border:1px solid orange}";
  let styles = [];
  for (let ev in dom.eventHandlers) {
    for (let sel in dom.eventHandlers[ev]) {
      dom.eventHandlers[ev][sel].delegates.forEach(function (del) {
        styles.push(dom.delegateFullSelector(del) + styleAttribs);
        // styles.push( del._fullSelector.trim() + styleAttribs2 );
      });
    }
  }
  $("#adobeopt-diag-css-styles").remove();
  $("head").append('<style id="adobeopt-diag-css-styles">' + styles.join("\n") + "</style>");
  dom.diag(styles);
}


tag.delegateHandlers = { /* click: { delegates:[] } */ }; // click, submit, etc

let elementsWithProps = [];
let elementProps = [];
let elementPropsAll = [];
const dynamicSelectorOperator = "~~";

// dynamic selectors; uses delimiter (~~) to denote static selector, delegate container selector and delegate target selector
tag.selectorFromDynSelector = function( dynSelector ) {
    return dynSelector.split(dynamicSelectorOperator).join(" ");
};

tag.parseDynSelector = function( dynSelector, props ) {
    let selectorParts = dynSelector.split(dynamicSelectorOperator);
    props._fullSelector = tag.selectorFromDynSelector( dynSelector );
    props._rootSelector = selectorParts.shift().trim() || "body"; // review: should be attached to child whenever possible
    if ( selectorParts.length == 2 ) {
        props._containerSelector = selectorParts.shift().trim();
        props._elementSelector = props._containerSelector + " " + selectorParts.shift().trim();
    } else if ( selectorParts.length == 1 ) {
        props._elementSelector = selectorParts.shift().trim();
    }
}

// delegate listener support

tag.addListener = tag.listen = function( eventName, dynSelector, props ) {
    props = adobeopt.extend( { }, props ); // make a copy
    tag.parseDynSelector( dynSelector, props );
    let rootDelegate = tag.addListenerRoot( eventName, props._rootSelector );
    if ( rootDelegate ) {
        rootDelegate.delegates.push( props );
    }
};

tag.addListenerRoot = function( eventName, selector ) {
    if ( ! tag.delegateHandlers.hasOwnProperty(eventName) ) {
        tag.delegateHandlers[eventName] = {};
    }
    let rootDelegate = tag.delegateHandlers[eventName][selector];
    if ( rootDelegate == undefined ) {
        let attach = document.querySelectorAll( selector );
        if ( attach.length == 0 ) {
            tag.log("warning: not elements found", selector);
            return null;
        }
        tag.delegateHandlers[eventName][selector] = rootDelegate = {
            eventName: eventName,
            delegates: [],
            listener: function( event ) { tag.dispatchDelegate( this, event, rootDelegate ) } // closure for this delegate root
        }
        attach.forEach( ( element ) => {
            element.addEventListener( eventName, rootDelegate.listener, { collect:true } ); // passive:true, 
        });
    }
    return rootDelegate;
}

tag.dispatchDelegate = function( element, event, delegateSet ) {
    tag.log("root delegate hit", delegateSet.eventName );

    delegateSet.delegates.forEach( function( props ) {
        let container = null;
        let delegateElement = element;
        if ( props._elementSelector ) {
            delegateElement =  dom.query(event.target).closest( props._elementSelector ).firstNode();
            if ( delegateElement == undefined ) {
                tag.log( "did not match elementSelector", props );
                return;
            }
        }
        if ( typeof props._containerSelector === "string" ) {
            container = event.target.closest( props._containerSelector );
            if ( container == null ) {
                tag.log( "did not match parentSelector", props ); // shouldn't be possible
                container = delegateElement;
            }
            props._container = container;
        }
        var context = {
            props: props,
            event: event, // for template references
            target: event.target, // for template references
            root: element,
            container: container,
            element: delegateElement,
            _cancelBeacon: false
        };
        tag.log( "matched elementSelector", props );
        try {
            ( context.props._fire || tag.fireContextProps )( props, context );
        } catch ( ex ) { tag.log( ex ) }
    });
};

// firing triggered values
tag.fireContextProps = function( props, context ) {
    tag.log( "fireContextProps", context );
    if ( context._cancelBeacon == true ) {
        tag.log("canceling per context._cancelBeacon");
        return;
    }
    context.props = adobeopt.extend( { }, props ); // make a copy for resolving
    tag.resolveValues( context, context.props );
    context.props.event = context.event;
    context.props.element = context.element;
    digitalDataEvents.push( context.props );
};

tag.closestAttr = function( element, attrName, def ) {
    if ( ! adobeopt.isJqueryLoaded() ) {
      return
    }
    let selector = "[" + sttrName + "]";
    try {
        return $(element).closest(selector).attr(attrName) || def;
    } catch ( ex ) { tag.log(ex) }
};

// diagnostic functions

tag.diagShowTagging = function() {
    let css = elementPropsAll.forEach( (props) => { $(props._fullSelector).css("border","1px solid red").css("background-color","red").css("padding","2px") } );
};


// placeholder functions

reco.addCarousel = function (response, element, selector) {
  try {
    var caroID = response.name + "-carousel";
    var reco = JSON.parse(response.options[0].content);
    reco.options.placementId = caroID;
    adobeopt.dictFromCssStr(element.dataset.mboxphOptions, reco.options); // [data-mboxph-options]
    $(element).append('<div id="' + caroID + '"></div>'); // wrapper for result
    merkle.reco.displayResults(reco);
  } catch (ex) { }
}

reco.regionalProdId = function (prodid) {
  if (digitalDataEx.site_store != "bd") {
    return prodid;
  }
  return prodid + "-" + digitalDataEx.memberDeliveryWH;
}

adobeopt.unknown = function (o) {
  dom.diag("unknown handler", o);
}

adobeopt.push = function (obj) {
  if (Array.isArray(obj)) {
    obj.forEach((aobj) => tag.applyObj(aobj));
  }
  tag.applyObj(obj);
}

dom.handleJsonOffer = function (response, element, selector) {
  var content = adobeopt.deepRef(response, "options.0.content", "").trim();
  if (content.indexOf('data-aopt-type="reco.addCarousel"') == - 1) {
    return false;
  }
  try {
    var jsoncontent = JSON.parse(response.options[0].content);
    var caroID = response.name + "-carousel";
    reco.options.placementId = caroID;
    adobeopt.dictFromCssStr(element.dataset.mboxphOptions, reco.options); // [data-mboxph-options]
    $(element).append('<div id="' + caroID + '"></div>'); // wrapper for result
    merkle.reco.displayResults(jsoncontent);
  } catch (ex) { adobeopt.aoptdiag(ex) }
}

dom.initContent = function (modname, props) {
  let m = adobeopt.module(modname, props);
  if (m.dataType == "domRecoJson" && m.recoJsonSelector !== undefined) {
    try {
      m.data = JSON.parse(document.querySelector(m.recoJsonSelector).textContent);
    } catch (e) {
      m.error("bad json response"); // report corrupt json
      return;
    }
  }
  let initContentType = true;
  // you can pre-iniitalize the module and supply a "initContent" function
  // to filter and/or replace the content. return false to prevent default content init
  if (typeof m.initContent === "function") {
    m.trySafe("m.initContent", function () {
      initContentType = m.initContent(m);
    });
    if (initContentType === false) {
      return;
    }
  }
  switch (m.contentType) {
    case "carousel":
      merkle.reco.displayResults(m.data);
      break;
    default:
      m.error("bad contentType");
  }
}


if ( _satellite.getVar("useAlloyTarget")) {

  dom.processPlaceholders = function (requestGlobalMbox) {

    var goreq = { request: { execute: { mboxes: [] } } };
    var mboxes = goreq.request.execute.mboxes;
    var mbxarr = document.querySelectorAll("[data-mboxph-name]:not([data-mboxph-status])"); // if they have [data-mboxph-status] they are already processing/processed

    mbxarr.forEach(function (mbxele) {
      let options = adobeopt.dictFromCssStr(mbxele.dataset.mboxphOptions);
      if (options.reqdata == "yes") {
        let datamboxargs = {
          index: mboxes.length,
          name: mbxele.dataset.mboxphName + "-data",
          parameters: adobeopt.dictFromCssStr(mbxele.dataset.mboxphParams) // [data-mboxph-params]
        };
        if (options.exclude == "cart") {
          let cartprods = adobeopt.deepRef(window, "digitalData.cart.products", []).map(function (prod) { return reco.regionalProdId(prod.id) }).join(",");
          datamboxargs.parameters.excludedIds = cartprods;
        }
        if (options.catid == "linktag") {
          datamboxargs.parameters['entity.categoryId'] = digitalDataEx.pageLinkTag;
          datamboxargs.parameters['entity.event.detailsOnly'] = true;
        }
        if (options.catid == "statelinktag") {
          datamboxargs.parameters['entity.categoryId'] = digitalDataEx.memberState + "-" + digitalDataEx.pageLinkTag;
          datamboxargs.parameters['entity.event.detailsOnly'] = true;
        }
        mboxes.push(datamboxargs);
      }
      let params = adobeopt.dictFromCssStr(mbxele.dataset.mboxphParams);
      mbxele.dataset.mboxphName.split(",").forEach(function (mboxname) {
        mboxes.push({
          index: mboxes.length,
          name: mboxname,
          parameters: params // [data-mboxph-params]
        });
      });
      mbxele.dataset.mboxphStatus = "requested";
    });
    if (mboxes.length == 0) {
      return;
    }
    adobe.target.getOffers(goreq)
  };
  adobeopt.logTargetActivity = function (response) {
    window.ttMETA = window.ttMETA || [];
    let ttMETA = window.ttMETA;
    if (response?.propositions && response?.propositions.length > 0) {
      response?.propositions.forEach((proposition) => {
        let activity = {};
        if (proposition?.items && proposition?.items.length > 0) {
          proposition.items.forEach((item, i) => {
            if (i === 0 && item?.meta && Object.keys(item?.meta).length > 0) {
              activity = { ...item.meta };
            } else {
              activity.activityId = proposition?.scopeDetails?.activity?.id;
            }
          });
        }
        ttMETA.push(activity);
      });
    }
  };
} else { // useAlloyTarget == false

  dom.processPlaceholders = function (requestGlobalMbox) {

    var goreq = { request: { execute: { mboxes: [] } } };
    var mboxes = goreq.request.execute.mboxes;
    var mbxarr = document.querySelectorAll("[data-mboxph-name]:not([data-mboxph-status])"); // if they have [data-mboxph-status] they are already processing/processed

    mbxarr.forEach(function (mbxele) {
      let options = adobeopt.dictFromCssStr(mbxele.dataset.mboxphOptions);
      if (options.reqdata == "yes") {
        let datamboxargs = {
          index: mboxes.length,
          name: mbxele.dataset.mboxphName + "-data",
          parameters: adobeopt.dictFromCssStr(mbxele.dataset.mboxphParams) // [data-mboxph-params]
        };
        if (options.exclude == "cart") {
          let cartprods = adobeopt.deepRef(window, "digitalData.cart.products", []).map(function (prod) { return reco.regionalProdId(prod.id) }).join(",");
          datamboxargs.parameters.excludedIds = cartprods;
        }
        if (options.catid == "linktag") {
          datamboxargs.parameters['entity.categoryId'] = digitalDataEx.pageLinkTag;
          datamboxargs.parameters['entity.event.detailsOnly'] = true;
        }
        if (options.catid == "statelinktag") {
          datamboxargs.parameters['entity.categoryId'] = digitalDataEx.memberState + "-" + digitalDataEx.pageLinkTag;
          datamboxargs.parameters['entity.event.detailsOnly'] = true;
        }
        mboxes.push(datamboxargs);
      }
      let params = adobeopt.dictFromCssStr(mbxele.dataset.mboxphParams);
      mbxele.dataset.mboxphName.split(",").forEach(function (mboxname) {
        mboxes.push({
          index: mboxes.length,
          name: mboxname,
          parameters: params // [data-mboxph-params]
        });
      });
      mbxele.dataset.mboxphStatus = "requested";
    });
    if (mboxes.length == 0) {
      return;
    }
    adobe.target.getOffers(goreq).then(function (response) {
      response.execute.mboxes.forEach(function (el) {
        let applyArgs = {
          response: {
            execute: {
              mboxes: [el]
            }
          }
        };
        let selector = '[data-mboxph-name="' + el.name + '"]';
        let mbxele = document.querySelector(selector);
        if (mbxele != null) {
          mbxele.dataset.mboxphStatus = "applied";
          applyArgs.selector = selector;
          if (dom.handleJsonOffer(el, mbxele, selector)) {
            mbxele.dataset.mboxphStatusDet = "jsonOffer";
            return;
          }
        }
        adobe.target.applyOffers(applyArgs);
      });
    });
  }
  // when all conditions are met process placeholders
  Promise.all([
    adobeopt.when.jQueryReady(),
    adobeopt.when.targetReady(),
    adobeopt.when.domReady(),
  ]).then(() => {
    adobeopt.dom.processPlaceholders();
    setTimeout(adobeopt.dom.processPlaceholders, 2000); // again after dynamic content loads    
  });

}

window.digitalDataEx = window.digitalDataEx || {};

(digitalDataEx.init = function (ddex) {

  let modLaunch = adobeopt.module("launch");

  modLaunch.trySafe("digitalDataEx:site", function () {

    let host = window.location.hostname.toLowerCase();

    ddex.siteLang = adobeopt.deepRef(window, "digitalData.siteLang") ||
      adobeopt.tag.getObjRef(window, "wcs.locale", document.cookie.indexOf("selectedLanguage=-25") > -1 ? "fr" : "en").slice(0, 2);
    try {
      ddex.memberLoggedIn = COSTCO.util.getMemberCookie().signedIn ? "yes" : "no";
    } catch (ex) {
      ddex.memberLoggedIn = document.cookie.indexOf("hashedUserId") > -1 ? "yes" : "no";
    }

    let domainCountry = host.slice(-4) == ".com" ? "us" : "ca";

    ddex.siteReleaseEnv = "prod";
    ddex.siteCountry = domainCountry;
    ddex.siteStore = "unknown";
    if (host == "www.costco.com" || host == "www.costco.ca") {
      ddex.siteStore = "bc";
    } else if (host == "www.costcobusinessdelivery.com" || host == "www.costcobusinesscentre.ca") {
      ddex.siteStore = "bd";
    } else {
      ddex.siteReleaseEnv = "nonprod";
      let otcode = document.querySelector("script[data-domain-script]")?.getAttribute("data-domain-script"); // use One Trust Script Attribute
      if (typeof otcode === "string") {
        otcode = otcode.replace("-test", "");
      }
      switch (otcode) {
        case "2653cf4b-5c84-40d7-a99b-fa6e1592503b":
          ddex.siteCountry = "us";
          ddex.siteStore = "bc";
          break;
        case "4325a455-ccf4-4ed6-854d-e9f4af4f7c2b":
          ddex.siteCountry = "ca";
          ddex.siteStore = "bc";
          break;
        case "5f812302-3833-47ab-8d40-4ee9060c2f41":
          ddex.siteCountry = "us";
          ddex.siteStore = "bd";
          break;
        case "d0af1630-fb74-4e09-969b-ae4f627acea8":
          ddex.siteCountry = "ca";
          ddex.siteStore = "bd";
          break;
      }
      if (ddex.siteStore === "unknown") {
        switch (host) {
          case "ca-stage.ecom.costco.com":
            ddex.siteCountry = "ca";
            ddex.siteStore = "bc";
            break;
        }
      }
    }
    ddex.siteStoreCountry = ddex.siteStore + ddex.siteCountry;
    ddex.siteStoreCountryLang = ddex.siteStore + ddex.siteCountry + ddex.siteLang;

    ddex.siteTargetPreview = "no";
    if (document.cookie.split(';').some(function (cookie) { return cookie.trim().startsWith('at_qa_mode='); })) {
      ddex.siteTargetPreview = "yes";
    }
  });

  modLaunch.trySafe("digitalDataEx:profile", function () {

    ddex.siteLoc = "unknown";
    try {
      if (ddex.siteStore === "bd") {
        let WC_BD_WHS = _satellite.cookie.get("WC_BD_WHS");
        if (typeof WC_BD_WHS == "string" && WC_BD_WHS.length > 0) {
          ddex.siteLoc = WC_BD_WHS;
        }
      } else {
        ddex.siteLoc = adobeopt.jsonCookieRef("WAREHOUSEDELIVERY_WHS", "nearestWarehouse.catalog");
      }
    } catch (ex) { modTarget.exception("profile:store",ex) }

    if (ddex.siteStore == "bd") {
      ddex.memberDeliveryWH = _satellite.cookie.get("WC_BD_WHS");
    } else {
      ddex.memberDeliveryWH = adobeopt.jsonCookieRef('WAREHOUSEDELIVERY_WHS', "groceryCenters.0", "unknown");
      ddex.memberState = _satellite.cookie.get("invCheckStateCode") || "unknown";
    }

  });

  modLaunch.trySafe("digitalDataEx:page", function () {
    ddex.pageType = adobeopt.deepRef(window, "digitalData.pageType", "Unknown");

    if ( ddex.pageType == "Unknown" ) {
      if (window.location.pathname.indexOf(".product.") > -1) {
        ddex.pageType = "Product Detail";
      } else if (window.location.pathname == "/") {
        ddex.pageType = "Home Page";
      } else if (adobeopt.deepRef(window, "digitalData.pageType")) {
        ddex.pageType = digitalData.pageType;
      } else if (adobeopt.deepRef(window, "digitalData.page.pageType")) {
        ddex.pageType = digitalData.page.pageType;
      } else if (adobeopt.deepRef(window, "pageAnalyticsInfo.pageType")) {
        ddex.pageType = window.pageAnalyticsInfo.pageType;
      }
    }
    if ( ddex.pageType == "Product Detail" ) {
      ddex.pagePdpProductId = digitalData?.product?.pid; // adobeopt.reExtract(/\.product\.(.*)\.html/, document.querySelector('link[rel="canonical"]')?.getAttribute("href") || "");
      if (!ddex.pagePdpProductId) {
        ddex.pagePdpProductId = window.location.pathname.split(".product.")[1].split(".html")[0];
      }
      ddex.pagePdpProductIdTarget = ddex.pagePdpProductId;
      if (ddex.siteStore === "bd") {
        ddex.pagePdpProductIdTarget += "-" + ddex.siteLoc;
      }
    }
    ddex.pageLinkTag = adobeopt.linkTag(window.location.pathname);

  });

  modLaunch.trySafe("digitalDataEx:session", function () {
    let modSession = adobeopt.module("session");
    modSession.msExpireAfter = 1200000; // 20 minutes, ms, 20 * 60 * 1000
    let session = adobeopt.json(sessionStorage.getItem("aoptSession"), {});
    if (session.sessionLastPageView === undefined || Date.now() - session.sessionLastPageView > modSession.msExpireAfter) {
      session.initType = session.sessionStartMs === undefined ? "new" : "expired";
      session.sessionNumber = adobeopt.deepRef(session, "sessionNumber", 0) + 1;
      session.sessionPageCount = 1;
      session.sessionStartMs = Date.now();
    } else {
      session.initType = "inc page";
      session.sessionPageCount += 1;
    }
    session.sessionLastPageView = Date.now();
    sessionStorage.setItem("aoptSession", JSON.stringify(session));
    ddex.session = modSession.session = session;
    modSession.diag("init", session);

    let landingPageProps = adobeopt.json(sessionStorage.getItem("landingPage"));
    if (landingPageProps === null || session.sessionPageCount === 1) {
      landingPageProps = {
        referrer: document.referrer,
        href: window.location.href,
        search: window.location.search
      }
      sessionStorage.setItem("landingPage", JSON.stringify(landingPageProps));
    }
    ddex.sessionLandingPage = landingPageProps;
    ddex.sessionLaunchPageCt = session.sessionPageCount;

    modSession.expireSession = function () {
      modSession.session.sessionLastPageView -= modSession.msExpireAfter + 60000; // plus one minute
      sessionStorage.setItem("aoptSession", JSON.stringify(modSession.session));
    }
  });

  modLaunch.trySafe("digitalDataEx:favcat", function () {

    let modSubCatFavs = adobeopt.module("subCatFavs");

    if (digitalDataEx.sessionLaunchPageCt === 1) {
      modSubCatFavs.diag("new session, removing subCatVisits-overall");
      sessionStorage.removeItem("subCatVisits-overall"); // will force recalculation on first catagory view
      sessionStorage.removeItem("subCatScores-overall");
    }

    function sortByProperty(inProp) {
      return function (a, b) {
        if (a[inProp] > b[inProp])
          return -1;
        else if (a[inProp] < b[inProp])
          return 1;

        return 0;
      }
    }

    scScores = window.localStorage.getItem("subCatScores-overall");

    if (!scScores) {
      window.sessionStorage.setItem("subCatScores-overall", "no scores");
      return "exiting : no scores";
    }
    window.sessionStorage.setItem("subCatScores-overall", scScores);
    if (scScores === "no scores") {
      return "m.scScores === no scores";
    }
    scScores = adobeopt.json(scScores, "no scores");
    if (typeof scScores !== "object") {
      return "m.scScores parse not object";
    }
    scSortList = [];
    var scItem;
    Object.keys(scScores).forEach(function (key) {
      scItem = {};
      scItem.subCat = key;
      scItem.score = scScores[key];
      if (!scItem.score || isNaN(scItem.score)) {
        scItem.score = 0;
      }
      scSortList.push(scItem);
    });
    scSortList.sort(sortByProperty("score"));

    let favCats = [];
    let favCatsAll = [];
    let favCatsAllLen = 0;

    scSortList.forEach(function (favcat, i) {
      if (favcat.score > 0) {
        favCats.push(favcat.subCat);
        ddex["memberFavSubCat" + (i > 0 ? i + 1 : "")] = favcat.subCat;
      }
      if ( favCatsAllLen + favcat.subCat.length < 254 ) { // max target profile value length
        favCatsAllLen += favcat.subCat.length + 1; // +1 for comma
        favCatsAll.push(favcat.subCat);
      }
      
    });
    ddex.memberFavSubCatsAll = favCatsAll.join(",");
    ddex.memberFavSubCats = ddex.memberFavSubCatsAll; // same value

  });

  modLaunch.diag("digitalDataEx", ddex);

})(window.digitalDataEx);


modTarget.trySafe("initMeta", function () {

  window.ttMETA = window.ttMETA || [];

  document.addEventListener("at-request-succeeded", function (e) {
    var tokens = e.detail.responseTokens;
    if (!adobeopt.isEmpty(tokens)) {
      tokens.forEach(function (token) {
        var props = {
          'CampaignName': token["activity.name"],
          'CampaignId': token["activity.id"],
          'RecipeName': token["experience.name"],
          'RecipeId': token["experience.id"],
          'OfferId': token["option.id"],
          'OfferName': token["option.name"],
          'LatestEMID': token["profile.LatestEMID"],
          'MboxName': e.detail.mbox
        };
        window.ttMETA.push(props);
        modTarget.diag("at-request-succeeded", props);
      });
    }
  });

  if (adobeopt.isDiag) {
    modTarget.events = ["at-library-loaded", "at-request-start", "at-request-succeeded", "at-request-failed", "at-content-rendering-start", "at-content-rendering-succeeded", "at-content-rendering-failed", "at-content-rendering-no-offers", "at-content-rendering-redirect"];
    modTarget.diag("diag:is adobe inited", window.adobe !== undefined, adobeopt.deepRef(window, "adobe.target.events") !== undefined);

    let ttMetaEvent = function (e) { modTarget.diag("event", e) };
    for (var adobe_msg in modTarget.events) {
      document.addEventListener(adobe_msg, ttMetaEvent);
    }
  }

  return "complete";

});

modTarget.trySafe("targetPageParamsAll:init", function () {

  function linkTag(l) {
    l = l.replace("https://", "").replace("http://", "");
    var ich = l.indexOf("/");
    if (ich === -1) {
      return "";
    }
    l = l.slice(ich + 1);
    return l.replace(".html", "");
  }

  var params = {};

  params.site_country = digitalDataEx.siteCountry;
  params.site_lang = digitalDataEx.siteLang;
  params.site_loggedin = digitalDataEx.memberLoggedIn;
  params.site_store = digitalDataEx.siteStore;
  params.site_storecountry = digitalDataEx.siteStoreCountry;
  params.site_loc = digitalDataEx.siteLoc;
  params.server_env = digitalDataEx.siteReleaseEnv;
  params.profile = {};

  params["profile.lastLinktag"] = digitalDataEx.pageLinkTag;

  if (digitalDataEx.pageType === "unknown") {
    digitalDataEx.pageType = adobeopt.deepRef(window, "PageAnalyticsInfo.pageType", adobeopt.deepRef(window, "digitalData.pageType", "unknown"));
  }

  params.page_type = digitalDataEx.pageType;
  if (params.page_type == "Product Detail") {
    params["entity.id"] = digitalDataEx.pagePdpProductIdTarget;
  } else if (digitalDataEx.pageType == "Category") {
    // params.user.categoryId = linkTag( window.location.pathname ) };
    // params.currentCategory = linkTag( window.location.pathname );
  }

  let favCat = adobeopt.deepRef(window, "digitalDataEx.memberFavSubCat", "");
  if (favCat !== "") {
    params["profile.favSubCat"] = favCat;
    params.favSubCat = favCat;
  }
  favCat = adobeopt.deepRef(window, "digitalDataEx.memberFavSubCat2", "");
  if (favCat !== "") {
    params["profile.favSubCat2"] = favCat;
  }
  favCat = adobeopt.deepRef(window, "digitalDataEx.memberFavSubCat3", "");
  if (favCat !== "") {
    params["profile.favSubCat3"] = favCat;
  }
  favCat = adobeopt.deepRef( window, "digitalDataEx.memberFavSubCat4", "" );
  if ( favCat !== "" ) {
    params["profile.favSubCat4"] = favCat;
  }
  favCat = adobeopt.deepRef( window, "digitalDataEx.memberFavSubCat5", "" );
  if ( favCat !== "" ) {
    params["profile.favSubCat5"] = favCat;
  }
  let favCats = adobeopt.deepRef( window, "digitalDataEx.memberFavSubCats", "" );
  if ( favCats !== "" ) {
    params["profile.favSubCats"] = favCats;
    params["profile.favSubCatsTop5"] = favCats.split(",").slice(0,5).join(",");
  }
  let memberFavSubCatsAll = adobeopt.deepRef( window, "digitalDataEx.memberFavSubCatsAll", "" );
  if ( memberFavSubCatsAll !== "" ) {
    params["profile.favSubCatsAll"] = memberFavSubCatsAll;
  }

  if (adobeopt.deepRef(window, "digitalDataEx.memberState", "")) {
    params["profile.whState"] = adobeopt.deepRef(window, "digitalDataEx.memberState", "");
    params["profile.lastStateLinktag"] = params["profile.whState"] + "-" + digitalDataEx.pageLinkTag;
    if ( params["profile.favSubCat"] !== undefined ) {
      params["profile.stateFavSubCat"] = params["profile.whState"] + "-" + params["profile.favSubCat"];
    }
  }

  params["profile.memberPrimaryPostal"] = _satellite.cookie.get("memberPrimaryPostal");
  params["profile.invCheckPostalCode"] = _satellite.cookie.get("invCheckPostalCode");
  params["profile.storeCity"] = adobeopt.jsonCookieRef('STORELOCATION',"storeLocation.city");
  params["profile.storeZip"] = adobeopt.jsonCookieRef('STORELOCATION',"storeLocation.zip");
  
  // let aopt_atpropertyid = adobeopt.queryParam("aopt_atpropertyid");
  // if ( typeof aopt_atpropertyid == "string" ) {
  //   if ( aopt_atpropertyid === "default" || aopt_atpropertyid === "" ) {
  //     localStorage.removeItem("aopt_target_property_id");
  //   } else {
  //     if ( aopt_atpropertyid == "contentstack" ) {
  //       aopt_atpropertyid = "cc746140-05e7-f5cd-4b25-b9168ccaabb9";
  //     } else if ( aopt_atpropertyid == "travel" ) {
  //       aopt_atpropertyid = "14a17a47-1494-9a74-372c-0c75326dd887";
  //     }
  //     localStorage.setItem("aopt_target_property_id", aopt_atpropertyid );
  //   }
  // }
  // let atPropertyIdLs = localStorage.getItem("aopt_target_property_id");
  // if ( typeof atPropertyIdLs === "string" ) {
  //   params.at_property = atPropertyIdLs;
  // }
  
  modTarget.targetPageParamsData = params;

  modTarget.diag("targetPageParams:calculated", modTarget.targetPageParamsData);

  window.targetPageParamsAll = function () {
    modTarget.diag("targetPageParamsAll:call", modTarget.targetPageParamsData);
    // only available at docReady
    if (window.location.pathname == "/CheckoutCartDisplayView" || window.location.pathname == "/CheckoutConfirmationView_v2") {
      let products = adobeopt.deepRef(window, "digitalData.cart.products");
      if (Array.isArray(products)) {
        modTarget.targetPageParamsData.cartIds = products.map(function (prod) { return prod.id }).join(",");
      }
    }
    return modTarget.targetPageParamsData;
  };

});

adobeopt.fixUpDigitalData = function () {

  function hasValueDd(v, fncTrue) {
    switch (typeof v) {
      case "string":
        if (v.length == 0 || v == "na") {
          return false;
        }
      case "number":
      case "boolean":
      case "bigint":
        if (typeof fncTrue == "function") {
          fncTrue(v);
        }
        return true;
    }
    return false;
  };

  modTarget.trySafe("aopt:fixUpDigitalData", function () {

    // fix up digitalData for backward compatibility

    let dd = window.digitalData;
    if (dd === undefined && (window.location.pathname === "/CheckoutConfirmationView_v2" || window.location.pathname === "/CheckoutConfirmationView")) {
      // find broken digitalData script & fix it
      modTarget.log("fixUpDigitalData:order conf missing dd");
      let elements = document.querySelectorAll("script");
      for (let i = 0; i < elements.length; i++) {
        let element = elements[i];
        let elementText = element.text;
        if (elementText.indexOf("window.digital" + "Data = {") > 1 && elementText.indexOf("orderText" + "Opt:") > 1) {
          modTarget.log("fixUpDigitalData:order conf: fixing missing dd");
          let result = elementText.replace(/orderTextOpt: (\S*),/gm, 'orderTextOpt: "$1",');
          if (result !== elementText) {
            let script = document.createElement('script');
            script.setAttribute("id", "digitalDataFixed");
            script.textContent = result;
            element.after(script);
            modTarget.log(result);
            break;
          }
        }
      }
      dd = window.digitalData;
    }

    if (dd === undefined) {
      return;
    }
    if (!hasValueDd(dd.pageType)) {
      dd.pageType = adobeopt.deepRef(dd, "page.pageType");
    }
    if (!hasValueDd(dd.pageName)) {
      dd.pageName = adobeopt.deepRef(dd, "page.pageName");
    }

    if (dd.pageName === "Product Detail | na") {
      dd.pageName = "Product Detail | " + digitalDataEx.pagePdpProductId;
    }

    let product = dd.product; // PDP
    if (typeof product === "object") {
      if (Array.isArray(product)) {
        product = product[0];
      } else {
        dd.product = [product]; // make an array
      }
      if (!hasValueDd(product.id) && !hasValueDd(product.pid)) {
        product.id = digitalDataEx.pagePdpProductId;
        product.pid = digitalDataEx.pagePdpProductId;
      } else {
        if (!hasValueDd(product.id) && hasValueDd(product.pid)) {
          product.id = product.pid;
        }
      }
      if (!hasValueDd(product.itemNumber) && hasValueDd(product.sku)) {
        product.itemNumber = product.sku;
      } else {
        product.itemNumber = product.itemNumber || '';
        product.sku = product.sku || '';
      }
      if (!hasValueDd(product.name)) {
        try {
          product.name = document.querySelector('meta[property="og:title"]').getAttribute("content")
        } catch (e) { };
      }
    }

    // order conf
    if (window.location.pathname === "/CheckoutConfirmationView_v2" || window.location.pathname === "/CheckoutConfirmationView") {

      if (dd.products && adobeopt.deepRef(dd, "cart.products") === undefined) {
        dd.cart = { transactionId: dd.transactionId, products: dd.products };
      }
      if (Array.isArray(dd.products)) {
        dd.products.forEach(function (prod) {
          if (prod.id === undefined && prod.pid !== undefined) {
            prod.id = prod.pid;
          }
          if (prod.deliveryMethod === undefined && prod.cartShipMethod !== undefined) {
            prod.deliveryMethod = prod.cartShipMethod;
          }
        });
      }

    }

  });

};

if ( ! _satellite.getVar("isPageModernized?") ) {
  adobeopt.fixUpDigitalData();
  adobeopt.when.domReady(adobeopt.fixUpDigitalData);
}

// app detection
(function() {
    let costid = adobeopt.queryParam("COSTID");
    if ( typeof costid == "string" ) {
        if ( costid.startsWith( "androidapp" ) || costid.startsWith( "iosapp" ) ) {
            localStorage.setItem( "aopt-appPlatform", costid );
            return;
        }
    }
    if ( localStorage.getItem( "aopt-appPlatform" ) !== null ) {
        return;
    }
    if ( typeof window.Android != 'undefined' ) {
        localStorage.setItem( "aopt-appPlatform", "androidapp (detected)" );
    } else if ( typeof window.webkit != 'undefined' ) {
        localStorage.setItem( "aopt-appPlatform", "iosapp (detected)" );
    }
} )();

modTarget.trySafe("aopt:onAoptReady", function () {
  if (Array.isArray(window.onAoptReady)) {
    window.onAoptReady.forEach(function (notify) { try { notify() } catch (ex) { console.error(ex) } });
  }
  window.onAoptReady = {
    push: function (notify) { notify() }
  }
});
_satellite.track("aoptReady");
